__An idiots guide to being lazy in job submission__

2 methods:
1) Dependencies:

sbatch --dependency=afterok:<JOBID> Job_Script

Using jobscripts like:
/home/hb1g13/J0
which run scripts like:
/home/hb1g13/next2

2) Bash script
If there's no time constraint it keeps the job queue much tidier to automatically submit the next job every 24 hours or so:
/home/hb1g13/autojob

Auto generating files:
This scripts require folders of the next data and tidy files to exist:
I auto generate these using:
/home/hb1g13/bin/autonext20.sh
/home/hb1g13/bin/autodata20.sh
/home/hb1g13/bin/autotidy.sh
/home/hb1g13/bin/auto_change #Python script find and replace 
                             --> future put sed in .sh files

If after I generate the files I find I've fucked up a line in everyfile 
I use the sed command:

sed -i 's/orignal_string/replacement_string/g' file